# Noctorya - Shopify Dawn Fork Rules

NOTE: At dawn/ repo root. Cursor auto-loads from here. ../ prefixed paths refer to sibling dirs in NOCTORYA/ parent.

## Project

- Shopify Dawn fork. Dark theme. Brand concept: "The Minimal Black Gallery".
- Design system encoded in assets/brand-tokens.css (108 CSS custom properties).
- Branches: main (working code) + live/noctorya (production deploy target).
- All design values come from ../01_BLUEPRINT/Noctorya_MasterBlueprint_Part2_Design_Build.md.
  Section 11 is the design bible. NEVER invent values.

## Tech stack

- Shopify Liquid + pure CSS (no SCSS, no LESS) + vanilla JS (no jQuery).
- Self-hosted WOFF2: Bodoni Moda 400/500 + Inter 400/500/600. NEVER Google Fonts CDN.
- BEM naming for new components. Mobile-first media queries.
- Dawn breakpoints (DO NOT change): 0-749 mobile, 750-989 tablet, 990+ desktop.

## File structure

- Custom sections: sections/[kebab-name].liquid with full schema + presets.
- Custom snippets: snippets/[kebab-name].liquid.
- Custom CSS: assets/[component-name].css (one file per section or component).
- App overrides: assets/custom-app-overrides.css (Judge.me, Picture It AR, Wishlist Hero, Selleasy).
- Custom JS: assets/[component-name].js.
- NEVER modify Dawn core files unless the task explicitly says "modify Dawn X".

## CSS rules

- Reference vars from assets/brand-tokens.css: var(--color-bg-primary), var(--space-4), etc.
- NEVER redeclare a token already defined in brand-tokens.css.
- BEM convention:
  - Block: .product-card
  - Element: .product-card__title (double underscore)
  - Modifier: .product-card__title--featured (double hyphen)
- Mobile-first @media: default = mobile, then @media (min-width: 750px) tablet,
  @media (min-width: 990px) desktop.
- Component scoping: one CSS file per top-level section. File name matches:
  sections/trust-bar.liquid -> assets/trust-bar.css.
- NO inline styles except dynamic section padding (template-driven Liquid output).
- NO !important outside assets/custom-app-overrides.css (third-party namespace exception).
- Global rules belong in assets/base.css: -webkit-font-smoothing, -moz-osx-font-smoothing,
  font-optical-sizing: none, body line-height 1.7, letter-spacing 0.

## Liquid conventions

- Use {% render %} not {% include %} ({% include %} is deprecated).
- App blocks pattern inside custom sections: {%- when '@app' -%} {% render block %}.
- Multi-step string composition: {% capture %} ... {% endcapture %}.
- Single-value bindings: {% assign %}.
- Section padding mobile: desktop value times 0.75 via {{ desktop_pad | times: 0.75 | round: 0 }}.
- Schema settings for per-section editable values (Customizer); theme settings for global.
- Always include schema presets so the section is reusable in the theme editor.

## Naming conventions

- File names: kebab-case (.liquid, .css, .js). NEVER Title Case or ALL CAPS in filenames.
- CSS classes: BEM lowercase kebab-case.
- Schema setting IDs: snake_case (e.g., product_picker, color_accent).
- Liquid variable names: snake_case.
- JS variable names: camelCase. JS class names: PascalCase.

## Brand-tokens.css integration

- Load order in layout/theme.liquid: assets/base.css then assets/brand-tokens.css.
- brand-tokens.css contains :root custom properties PLUS a Dawn override block
  (:root, .color-scheme-1 { --color-background, --color-foreground, ... }).
- Component CSS references tokens via var(--foo); never redeclare or hard-code values.

## Voice canon for microcopy

- All customer-facing text follows the Noctorya voice canon (anonymous critic writing for Eleanor, the buyer persona)
  (../08_DEEP_RESEARCH/folder2_strategy/voice_canon.md).
- Cold, factual, manifesto-like. No marketing buzzwords.
- Second-person ("you", "your") banned in body copy; allowed in CTAs and headings only.
- ALL CAPS for headings/CTAs only; never for emphasis in body text.
- Title format: [Artist Last Name]: [Painting Title]. URL slug: artist-lastname-painting-name.

## Performance

- Hero image: loading="eager", fetchpriority="high".
- Collection grid: first 4 products loading="eager"; rest loading="lazy".
- All non-critical images: loading="lazy".
- JS scripts: defer or async by default; no synchronous third-party scripts.
- Font preload: 2 fonts only (inter-400.woff2 + bodoni-moda-500.woff2).
- font-display: swap for heading fonts; font-display: optional for body fonts.
- Lighthouse target: Mobile score >= 60 (Master Dispatcher Task 071).
- /links page: system fonts only, inline CSS in <style>, no external stylesheet, <2s LCP on 3G.

## Accessibility

- Semantic HTML: header, nav, main, section, article, footer.
  ARIA roles only when semantic element is insufficient.
- WCAG 2.4.7 focus indicators: BOTH outline AND box-shadow required (Windows High Contrast
  Mode suppresses shadows). See base.css :focus-visible.
- Touch targets: 48px minimum on mobile interactive elements.
- Color contrast: WCAG AA validated combinations documented in brand-tokens.css comments;
  do not pair tokens outside the validated set.
- Alt text: 80-125 chars, factual, includes artist + title + product type.

## NEVER DO

- NEVER use Bodoni Moda for body text. Headings >= 24px at weight 500+ only.
- NEVER use light backgrounds. Noctorya is dark from the ground up.
- NEVER use Google Fonts CDN. Self-hosted WOFF2 only.
- NEVER use jQuery. Dawn is vanilla JS.
- NEVER use localStorage or sessionStorage in Liquid context (unsupported in Shopify).
- NEVER use Google Tag Manager. Use native Google/Meta/TikTok channels.
- NEVER use emoji in code, comments, or filenames.
- NEVER use !important outside assets/custom-app-overrides.css.
- NEVER invent color, spacing, or typography values. Reference brand-tokens.css.
- NEVER use em dashes in customer-facing microcopy. Use period, comma, or colon.
- NEVER use dropdowns for product variants. Pills with dimensions AND price only.
- NEVER pre-select a size on variant selectors.
- NEVER skip WCAG focus indicators to save time.
- NEVER enable cart drawer on mobile <990px. Cart drawer is desktop-only;
  mobile redirects to /cart page via JS.
- NEVER create files outside the theme directory unless the task explicitly requests.

## When stuck

- Reference the specific Blueprint Part 2 section number in your question to Eduard.
- Check assets/brand-tokens.css for available tokens before requesting new values.
